<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n47142b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n47" href="#n47142b">N47 (VI.B.40)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n47all.htm#n47142b"> 142(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> maa kheru / true of voice</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The deceased whose heart or conscience had been weighed in the balance, and not found wanting, was declareed to be &ldquo;maa kheru&rdquo; <font color="green">[image]</font>, and in papyri these words always follow the names of the persons for which they were written. <small> E.A. Wallis Budge, <a name="BOD3" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#BOD3"><cite title="source">The Book of the Dead</cite></a>, 2nd Ed (1909) lxv</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
